  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Postpartum - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_postpartum">Postpartum</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_postpartum">Postpartum</xref>
 is the period of time immediately after childbirth, and is defined for the mother.  </p>
  <p>
For the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_maternity_services_data_set">Maternity Services Data Set</xref>
, the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_postpartum">Postpartum</xref>
 period will end following the mother's discharge from maternity services.   </p>
  <p>
Note: 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_postnatal">Postnatal</xref>
 is for the child.  </p>

